David Lyon, the APC candidate has been declared winner of the Bayelsa Nov. 16, 2019 governorship election.
The declaration was made Monday morning by the University of Benin vice chancellor and IBEC returning officer Prof. Faraday Orumwese.
He announced that Lyon polled 352,552 votes to defeat Duoye Diri of the PDP who polled 143, 172 votes.
The total number of registered voters was announced as 922, 562 and the accredited wwas 517,883

			
